    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1974-01-21T08:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1974-01-21T08:25:00-05:00" n="283"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                <head>283. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Saudi Arabia</gloss> to
                    the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d283fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, <persName corresp="#p_KHA1"
                            >Kissinger</persName> Office Files, Box 139, Country Files, Middle East,
                        Saudi Arabia, Dec 73–Feb 74. Secret; Niact; Immediate; <gloss
                            target="#t_Cherokee1">Cherokee</gloss>; <gloss target="#t_Nodis1"
                            >Nodis</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Jidda</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1974-01-21T13:25:00+00:00">January 21, 1974,
                        1325Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>328. <gloss target="#t_subj1">Subj</gloss>: Oil Deliveries to <gloss
                        target="#t_US1">U.S.</gloss> Fleets Stopped. <gloss target="#t_Ref1"
                        >Ref</gloss>: Jidda 5763.<note n="2" xml:id="d283fn2">
                        <ref target="#d275">Document 275</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_YAZ1">Ahmad Zaki Yamani</persName>, Saudi Minister of
                        Petroleum, who is back in Saudi Arabia for 36 hours asked urgently to see me
                        today.</item>
                    <pb facs="0838" n="800" xml:id="pg_800"/>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>He reviewed the decision that had been taken to resume oil deliveries to
                        the Sixth and Seventh Fleets, said that the only Saudis who knew of the
                        decision were the King and <persName corresp="#p_SBFBAAP1">Prince
                            Saud</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_YAZ1">Yamani</persName>’s deputy.
                        He had informed <persName corresp="#p_JF1">Frank Jungers</persName>
                        President of <gloss target="#t_ARAMCO1">Aramco</gloss> in the presence of
                            <persName corresp="#p_SBFBAAP1">Prince Saud</persName> of this decision
                        and asked that all oil transfers be outside Saudi Arabia; i.e. that no books
                        in Saudi Arabia would show that the deliveries had been made.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JF1">Jungers</persName>, however, called in the
                        Minister of Petroleum staff in Dhahran, told them that <persName
                            corresp="#p_YAZ1">Yamani</persName> had given orders that the <gloss
                            target="#t_US1">U.S.</gloss> fleet be supplied and instructed them to
                        handle deliveries accordingly. The Petroleum Ministry staff denied that such
                        an order existed; one senior staff member flew to Europe to question
                            <persName corresp="#p_YAZ1">Yamani</persName> who promptly denied that
                        there was any such order.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_YAZ1">Yamani</persName>, who said he was furious,
                        immediately summoned <persName corresp="#p_JF1">Jungers</persName> who met
                        with him in Madrid.<note n="3" xml:id="d283fn3">According to telegram 333
                            from Jidda, January 21, it appeared that by the time <persName
                                corresp="#p_JF1">Jungers</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_YAZ1"
                                >Yamani</persName> met in Madrid, the highest levels of <gloss
                                target="#t_ARAMCO1">ARAMCO</gloss> “may have known for more than a
                            week that oil deliveries agreement derailed.” (National Archives,
                                <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials,
                                <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 631, Country Files,
                            Middle East, Saudi Arabia, Vol. V)</note>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JF1">Jungers</persName> admitted he had erred; but the
                        damage was done.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_YAZ1">Yamani</persName> said he will take the matter
                        up again with the King “if I have time.”</item>
                    <label>6.</label>
                    <item>I said the action was deplorable and inexcusable, but the whole matter of
                        supplies to the fleets was now academic as the fleets could be supplied
                        normally when the boycott is lifted tomorrow. (<persName corresp="#p_YAZ1"
                            >Yamani</persName> said the boycott would not be lifted tomorrow. See
                        following cable.)<note n="4" xml:id="d283fn4">
                            <ref target="#d284">Document 284</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>7.</label>
                    <item>
                        <hi rend="italic">Comment:</hi>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JF1">Frank Jungers</persName> is an excellent
                        technician, but is not noted for his political astuteness. <gloss
                            target="#t_ARAMCO1">Aramco</gloss> had not told us of this decision, and
                        I assume the parent companies have not told the Department. It is just
                        conceivable that <gloss target="#t_ARAMCO1">Aramco</gloss> is trying to
                        conceal from us this action and Junger’s role in it until the boycott is
                        lifted, an action they are counting on very soon.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AJE1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Akins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
